-- Brazil’s BTG to Buy 30% Stake in Fitness Chains, Folha Reports
-- B y   C r i s t i a n e   L u c c h e s i
-- 2012-04-28T16:18:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-28/brazil-s-btg-to-buy-30-stake-in-fitness-chains-folha-reports.html
Banco BTG Pactual SA (BBTG11) , led by the
Brazilian billionaire Andre Esteves, will announce on April 30
the acquisition of 30 percent of the Brazilian physical-fitness
chains Bodytech and Formula, Folha de S. Paulo reported, citing
Luiz Urquiza, chief executive officer at Bodytech.  The value of the transaction won’t be disclosed, though
Folha reported, citing analysts, that BTG paid 200 million ($106
million) for the stake.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Cristiane Lucchesi in Sao Paulo at 
 clucchesi5@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net  